avdta.network

Class PathList

  • java.lang.Object
    • avdta.network.PathList

  • public class PathList
extends java.lang.Object
    This class contains a list of unique Path objects. It is intended to avoid creating duplicate Paths, which reduces memory as well as storage when saving assignments. The PathList contains methods to read and write from file. Paths are hashed according to origin, destination, and size to reduce the number of Path to Path comparisons.

    • Method Detail

      • addPath

        public Path addPath(Path p)
        This method attempts to add the Path to the list. If the Path already exists in this PathList, this method will return the existing Path. Otherwise, the new Path will be added. Calls to this method should use the return value as the assigned Path.
        Parameters:
        p - the Path to be added
        Returns:
        new path, or old path if new path is a duplicate

      • writeToFile

        public void writeToFile(Assignment assign)

        Parameters:
        assign - the Assignment
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if the file cannot be written

      • writeToFile

        public void writeToFile(java.io.File file)
                 throws java.io.IOException
        This method writes this PathList to a file. All saved Paths are written out as a list of Links. Path ids are saved, and Paths should be referenced by their id.
        Parameters:
        file - the File to save to
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if the file cannot be written

      • readFromFile

        public void readFromFile(Network network,
                         java.io.File file)
                  throws java.io.IOException
        This method constructs this PathList from the specified File. Paths in the file are converted to a list of Links via the specified Network. The file should not be modified outside of PathList. Loading a PathList from an externally modified file may result in corrupted data. The Network is needed because PathList saves Link ids, not Link objects.
        Parameters:
        network - the Network this PathList applies to.
        file - the File to read from
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if the File cannot be read

        This creates a map of ids to Paths to help restore assignments saved via Path ids.
        Returns:
        a mapping of ids to Paths
